<br>
This is not a voting thread.  No votes will be passed on what FCFS means, nor will it ever be voted on.  Your interpretation of FCFS may differ from others, but remember that the basic tenet of FCFS is respsect and should be a fundamental in it's application.<br>
<br>
That being said, the topic for today is the system of spawn organization known as First Come, First Serve.<br>
<br>
First Come, First Serve (FCFS), is an extension of the classic free for all system.  In it, spawns are not reserved or able to be held over a long term period of time.  Basically, the first group to a spawn gets to do it; those that come afterwards back off out of respect to the group that got there first.  This differs from the classic ffa in that in ffa, spawn clipping (taking a spawn while the original group is buffing/moving/cr'ing), cohing past the group, and other similiar tactics are present.  FCFS is characterized by respect of the group that got there first and are thus entitled to the spawn.<br>
<br>
Obviously, the conflict arises in deciding what constitutes &quot;being first&quot;.<br>
<br>
Many situations are to be considered such as...<br>
<br>
- The person who &quot;claims&quot; a spawn in /shout (particularily Lodizal and other one spawn mobs) and then begins gathering forces there.<br>
<br>
- The person who &quot;claims&quot; a spawn in /shout with people on the way.<br>
<br>
- The person who &quot;claims&quot; a spawn with part of their force present and the rest on the way.<br>
<br>
- The person who &quot;claims&quot; a spawn with all their force present but is contested with another group that has their force partially or fully present.<br>
<br>
Any definition of &quot;being first&quot; should include simple answer and reasoning to these questions.  <br>
<br>
Your thoughts and comments are, as always, appreciated.  Thanks.<br>
