Taeolin Retired Druid of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthorondar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorondar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/27/01 11:13:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/Hollywood/Hills/5539/cyclone2.jpg width=100 height=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Remember how you would like to be treated.</span><hr size=1> Is all I can say.  If you feel it's ok to jump ahead of a group that is recouping for their second try, or if you think that not asking them if you try your hand at a mob before engaging is ok, prepare yourself to be treated in the exact same manner.<br>
<br>
The more people that are not extended simple courtesies or consideration will become more people whom extending a simple courtesy or consideration will be hard for.  None of this would be an issue if people merely clarified their intents and/or asked for their shot, irregardless of whether or not you thought you were in the right, or were riteous in your actions.<br>
<br>
No?<br>
